          "tag": "payouts - threshold",
          "intent": "Payouts & Commission",
          "response": "Hey [Name],\n\nHere's how payouts work at IM8:\n\nWe pay out monthly — at the end of each calendar month, usually within two weeks. There's a 30-day hold on every sale (that's the refund window clearing), and a $100 USD minimum to trigger a payout. Anything under just rolls over — no expiry, no pressure.\n\nSo if you make a sale in January, the hold clears in February, and you'll see the payout in early March.\n\nOne thing to check first: your payout method needs to be set up in your SS dashboard or payments just queue up. You can sort it here: https://affiliates.socialsnowball.io/auth/affiliate/login\n\nLet me know if anything's not adding up.",
          "responseOriginal": "Hi [Name],\n\nHow payouts work:\n\n• Minimum: $100 USD\n• Schedule: Monthly — end of each calendar month, usually within two weeks\n• Commission hold: 30 days from the date of sale for a refund window to clear\n• Method: PayPal or bank transfer via your SS dashboard\n\nTimeline: sale in January → hold clears February → paid early March. You're typically looking at the month after next for any given sale.\n\nPayout method must be set up in your SS dashboard first — payments queue until it's done: https://affiliates.socialsnowball.io/auth/affiliate/login\n\nWith Health,\n[Your name]\nThe Affiliates Team @ IM8 Health",
